title: Sidewall
provenance: Easton's Castle, Aberdeen, South Dakota, a house built in 1889 and extensively renovated between 1902 and 1904.  This pattern was probably hung during the renovation.
description: Floral and foliate pattern in art nouveau style. Printed in green, red, and tan on a yellow ground,.
